[Auction "E"]
1NT pass 2C pass 2S pass 4NT pass 5C pass 5D pass 5S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "171538e8fcdbebb22dc1572ece0df278be7b72abba093fa6e0efaaeff70f7d97"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/roman_keycard"]
[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown.  

Partner has 15-17 points and 4 \Ss. You have 18 points and 4 \Ss. You plan to bid the slam, but first you check Key-Cards. So you bid 4NT. Partner says 5\C.  

You are missing 1 Key-Card. Slam has become less certain. You decide to see if partner has the trump Queen so you bid 5\D. Partner bids 5\S. What do you say next? 

Partner denies having the \SQ. Knowing that the best you could hope for would be a finesse to make the slam you give up your quest and pass.}

